                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/411: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-21T17:00:00-05:45"
                            >January 21, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:39 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. My telegram No. 15, January 16, 5 p.m.<note n="14b" xml:id="d650fn14b">Not
                        printed.</note> The boundary protocol was signed this afternoon. Its text
                    will not be made public here until after it has been submitted to Congress for
                    ratification.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
